---
const features = [
  {
    title: 'Config over code',
    body: 'One YAML per language project. Every stage reads the same validated config, writes a manifest, and is fully resumable. Re-run a stage without redoing the rest.',
    icon: '<path d="M4 5h16M4 12h10M4 19h16" stroke-linecap="round"/>',
  },
  {
    title: 'A language is a YAML',
    body: 'Adding a language is a config file: an ISO code, its script, and normalization rules. From that, <b>FineWeb-2</b> web text wires itself in automatically, and <b>Aya</b> native instruction data too where it exists, with no per-language plumbing. Current or future, every language gets it.',
    icon: '<path d="M7 3h8l4 4v13a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H7a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V4a1 1 0 0 1 1-1Z" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M14 3v5h5" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M12 11v6M9 14h6" stroke-linecap="round"/>',
  },
  {
    title: 'Adapt, don\'t pretrain',
    body: 'Continued pretraining + tokenizer extension + instruction tuning on a strong multilingual base: Llama, Qwen3, Gemma, Aya, XLM-R. Best quality per dollar, no from-scratch runs.',
    icon: '<path d="M12 3v18M5 8l7-5 7 5M5 16l7 5 7-5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>',
  },
  {
    title: 'Consumer-GPU first',
    body: 'QLoRA / 4-bit defaults that run on Colab, Kaggle, or an 8&nbsp;GB card. Automatic QLoRA→LoRA→CPU fallback when there\'s no GPU. A100 profiles &amp; SLURM job arrays scale it to a cluster.',
    icon: '<rect x="4" y="7" width="16" height="10" rx="2"/><path d="M8 7V5M16 7V5M9 17v2M15 17v2" stroke-linecap="round"/>',
  },
  {
    title: 'Provenance, licensing & ethics',
    body: 'Every datum carries a license and source record. Export is <b>blocked</b> until licenses resolve, then the release license is <b>computed automatically</b> (share-alike dominates permissive sources). Native-speaker review queues gate both data and model outputs.',
    icon: '<path d="M12 3l7 3v5c0 4.5-3 8-7 10-4-2-7-5.5-7-10V6l7-3Z" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>',
  },
  {
    title: 'Conversational data, four ways',
    body: 'Translate open instruction sets (NLLB, M2M-100, OPUS-MT, MADLAD), reuse <b>native instruction data</b> (Aya) as-is, synthesize with a local teacher, then review. All open-weight, no proprietary APIs, with FLORES-in-training safeguards.',
    icon: '<path d="M4 5h16v10H10l-4 4V5Z" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M8 9h8M8 12h5" stroke-linecap="round"/>',
  },
  {
    title: 'Evaluate honestly, everywhere',
    body: 'A <b>coverage-aware</b> harness: every benchmark self-reports whether it covers the language, scores are <b>base-vs-adapted deltas</b> with bootstrap CIs, and a universal corpus-derived <b>native-cloze</b> metric covers the long tail that has no benchmarks at all.',
    icon: '<path d="M4 19V5M4 19h16" stroke-linecap="round"/><rect x="7" y="11" width="3" height="5" rx="0.5"/><rect x="12" y="8" width="3" height="8" rx="0.5"/><rect x="17" y="13" width="3" height="3" rx="0.5"/>',
  },
  {
    title: 'Drive it from the dashboard',
    body: 'A Streamlit app: a wizard to generate a project, a run monitor with report cards, the review queue, and a chat window to talk to the model you just trained.',
    icon: '<rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="16" rx="2"/><path d="M3 9h18M8 13v3M12 12v4M16 14v2" stroke-linecap="round"/>',
  },
];
---
<section class="section" id="features">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Why lrl-toolkit</span>
      <h2>Built for the messy reality of low-resource languages.</h2>
      <p>Scattered corpora, varying scripts and dialects, and instruction data that barely exists, made into a managed, reproducible, one-config workflow.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="features">
      {features.map((f) => (
        <div class="feature reveal">
          <div class="ficon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" set:html={f.icon}></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>{f.title}</h3>
          <p set:html={f.body}></p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
